         <p>A Respite Admission supports the Caregiver(s) by providing temporary relief. This transfer of temporary care to the Nipigon Hospital can be for a variety of reasons including vacation, medical reasons, or for a much needed rest for the caregiver.</p>
         <h3>What is Respite?</h3>
         <p>A Respite admission is a preplanned admission for a client who may require or benefit from a short stay at the Nipigon Hospital and is expected to return to their home in the community within a specified period of time.</p>
         <h3>Applying for Respite</h3>
         <p>A client may apply for a maximum of 90 days or 13 weeks of Respite care each year. Starting with 1st day of stay The recommended minimum length of stay per admission is 1 week, but can be increased to a maximum of 30 days per admission. A variety of health care staff will care for your needs including RN's, RPN's and Activity Coordinator.</p>
         <p>Applications for Respite are initiated through your family physician, or yourself. A representative from Community Care Access Centre will contact you to complete the application process. Applications will then be submitted to Placement Co-ordination Services at 1-800-626-5406.</p>
