         <h3>What to Expect Upon Admission</h3>
         <p>On admission the client must bring their medications from home in the original containers (pill bottles). The purchase and delivery of any new medications prescribed during a Respite stay is the responsibility of the family.</p>
         <p>Please have all items of clothing labeled prior to admission. Personal hygiene products must also be brought from home.</p>
         <p>Valuable articles are considered the responsibility of the client and it is suggested that these be left at home. Should it be necessary to bring your valuables with you, ie. hearing aids, glasses, small amount of money, the hospital will, upon request, store valuables for safekeeping.</p>
         <p>A phone is available at bedside for local calls.</p>

         <h3>Cost of a Respite Admission</h3>
         <p>It has been predetermined by the Ministry of Health that a daily fee of $34.63, effective July 1st 2011, will be charged to the caregiver.</p>
         <p>The Ministry of Health increases fees on an annual basis.</p>

